h tragedy on the home front from afar. Gibson's religious beliefs significantly influenced and sustained him through his darkest hours. He felt himself a gentle man caught up "on an errand the full consequences of which we did not realize."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSoldierszCanadavCorrespondence. 0aSoldierszCanadavDiaries. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918vPersonal narratives, Canadian. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aHistory: Canadian History. 4aHistory: Military History. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Military.2bisacsh  a11th Brigade.  a4th Division.  a75th Battalion.  a9th Platoon.  aC Company.  aRegimental No. 787167.  aSection Bombers.1 aNewbold, K. Bruce, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNewbold, L. Iris, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWalters, Evelyn A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalters, Mark G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112346440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771123464423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771123464/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles